import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    box_plot = data.boxplot(column='Beak_Length__mm_', by='Species', grid=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Beak Length (mm) across different species?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Species')
    plt.ylabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        box_plot.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    male_data = data[data['Sex'] == 'male']
    female_data = data[data['Sex'] == 'female']
    
    plt.scatter(male_data['Beak_Depth__mm_'], male_data['Body_Mass__g_'], label='Male', alpha=0.5)
    plt.scatter(female_data['Beak_Depth__mm_'], female_data['Body_Mass__g_'], label='Female', alpha=0.5)
    
    plt.xlabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    plt.ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Beak Depth (mm) and Body Mass (g) for male and female penguins?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    islands = data['Island'].unique()
    for island in islands:
        island_data = data[data['Island'] == island]
        plt.hist(island_data['Flipper_Length__mm_'], alpha=0.5, label=island)
    
    plt.xlabel('Flipper Length (mm)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Island')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Flipper Length (mm) for each island?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the distribution of Body Mass (g) for male and female penguins?')

    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;
